1
00:01:25,390 --> 00:01:32,030
[Echoes of a Thousand Moons]

2
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:34,979
[Episode 11]

3
00:01:36,729 --> 00:01:37,780
I heard that

4
00:01:38,479 --> 00:01:39,350
recently in the concession,

5
00:01:39,350 --> 00:01:41,750
the streets are full of homeless refugees.

6
00:01:41,870 --> 00:01:44,789
Every night, there are people
who starve and freeze to death.

7
00:01:44,789 --> 00:01:46,680
Charity Hall even has a special corpse
transport team.

8
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:48,920
Every early morning,
they take the corpses

9
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:52,120
to the wilderness and bury them.

10
00:01:52,990 --> 00:01:53,470
No, no.

11
00:01:54,310 --> 00:01:55,240
Madam, don't...

12
00:01:55,479 --> 00:01:56,930
I didn't mean that.

13
00:01:57,310 --> 00:01:58,370
Master and Mrs. Liu

14
00:01:58,479 --> 00:02:00,500
will surely be blessed by God.

15
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:01,300
They will be fine.

16
00:02:01,300 --> 00:02:02,710
At most, Master…

17
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:05,450
Master must have been sick.

18
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:07,430
Otherwise, he would have come back
himself by now,

19
00:02:07,430 --> 00:02:08,080
right?

20
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:09,400
Mrs. Liu is so smart.

21
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:11,080
Master definitely won't suffer any losses.

22
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,240
Don't worry, Madam.

23
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:13,440
Tomorrow,

24
00:02:13,590 --> 00:02:14,910
I will go to the refugee shelter again

25
00:02:14,910 --> 00:02:16,070
and check one more time.

26
00:02:16,070 --> 00:02:17,000
All right.

27
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,320
Don't worry.

28
00:02:18,340 --> 00:02:19,740
Everything will be fine.

29
00:02:25,610 --> 00:02:26,310
What are you doing?

30
00:02:26,310 --> 00:02:26,840
Who is it?

31
00:02:26,870 --> 00:02:27,930
What are you doing?

32
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:29,240
Wanfu.

33
00:02:29,590 --> 00:02:30,430
Baozi?

34
00:02:30,860 --> 00:02:31,829
Baozi!

35
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:33,380
You're alive.

36
00:02:33,530 --> 00:02:34,610
Yes. Yes.

37
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:38,110
Wait, why are you in the concession?

38
00:02:38,110 --> 00:02:39,270
I'm smart.

39
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:40,360
I knew life outside became unsustainable.

40
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,240
So, before the concession was sealed off,

41
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:42,160
I sneaked in.

42
00:02:42,670 --> 00:02:43,850
Good job.

43
00:02:44,230 --> 00:02:45,360
You even gained weight.

44
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,290
Not bad.

45
00:02:48,340 --> 00:02:49,190
What's up?

46
00:02:50,290 --> 00:02:52,370
Shopkeeper died.

47
00:02:54,079 --> 00:02:54,840
I know.

48
00:02:55,190 --> 00:02:56,650
The shop was blown up too.

49
00:02:57,470 --> 00:02:58,079
I know.

50
00:02:58,079 --> 00:03:00,450
Your bridal chamber is gone.

51
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:04,870
Hurry. Hurry. Hurry.

52
00:03:04,870 --> 00:03:06,510
Call her Madam.

53
00:03:06,910 --> 00:03:07,990
Whose wife is this?

54
00:03:08,030 --> 00:03:09,370
None of your business.

55
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,260
Call her Madam.

56
00:03:12,310 --> 00:03:13,080
Madam.

57
00:03:14,420 --> 00:03:17,220
What are you doing in the concession?

58
00:03:17,670 --> 00:03:19,550
I'm working at Lutai Restaurant now.

59
00:03:19,550 --> 00:03:21,020
Since refugees are
flocking to the concession,

60
00:03:21,020 --> 00:03:23,190
the restaurant is doing extremely well.

61
00:03:23,190 --> 00:03:24,240
We're recruiting new employees right now.

62
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:25,079
We need a cook.

63
00:03:25,110 --> 00:03:26,540
We can provide room and board.

64
00:03:26,540 --> 00:03:28,270
You don't have a job now, do you?

65
00:03:28,350 --> 00:03:29,680
Come with me.

66
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:31,360
Where am I supposed to go with you?

67
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:32,820
I have a lot of things to do.

68
00:03:36,260 --> 00:03:36,940
Come here.

69
00:03:37,890 --> 00:03:38,960
Let me tell you,

70
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,390
I have to go to Wuhan.

71
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:42,740
Why are you going to Wuhan?

72
00:03:42,740 --> 00:03:43,870
Xiaoyue is in Wuhan.

73
00:03:44,060 --> 00:03:45,190
Why is Xiaoyue in Wuhan?

74
00:03:45,190 --> 00:03:46,960
Why do you have so many questions?

75
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:47,840
Listen to me.

76
00:03:48,590 --> 00:03:49,680
All the ships from Shanghai

77
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:51,520
to Wuhan have been suspended.

78
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,130
You've been in the concession
for a long time.

79
00:03:53,130 --> 00:03:54,250
Help me ask around

80
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:56,060
to see if there's any other way
to go to Wuhan.

81
00:03:56,060 --> 00:03:57,210
I'll come find you in a couple of days.

82
00:03:57,210 --> 00:03:58,820
What's the name of your restaurant?

83
00:03:58,820 --> 00:03:59,880
Lutai Restaurant.

84
00:04:00,030 --> 00:04:01,040
Lutai Restaurant.

85
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:02,770
Okay, I know the concession well.

86
00:04:02,770 --> 00:04:04,680
I'll find you after asking around.

87
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:05,560
You have to come visit me.

88
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:06,980
I will definitely visit you.

89
00:04:06,980 --> 00:04:07,860
It's a deal.

90
00:04:10,780 --> 00:04:12,380
It's good that you're alive.

91
00:04:14,030 --> 00:04:14,870
Bye.

92
00:04:16,329 --> 00:04:16,970
Don't forget to visit me.

93
00:04:16,970 --> 00:04:18,829
I'll visit you in a couple of days.

94
00:04:23,820 --> 00:04:24,430
Madam.

95
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,830
This is an old colleague
from my former restaurant.

96
00:04:26,830 --> 00:04:28,890
I didn't expect him to still be alive.

97
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,070
Wanfu.

98
00:04:30,390 --> 00:04:31,580
This is a good thing.

99
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:32,510
What's good?

100
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:33,600
Our family's affairs

101
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,390
have already delayed you for too long.

102
00:04:35,390 --> 00:04:37,190
I already felt a bit bad about it.

103
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,470
I promised

104
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:40,290
to give you a ferry ticket to Wuhan.

105
00:04:40,290 --> 00:04:41,440
Now that

106
00:04:43,430 --> 00:04:45,780
you met your friend here,

107
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,750
you can go to him,

108
00:04:47,770 --> 00:04:49,780
-Don't worry about our matters.
-Madam.

109
00:04:49,780 --> 00:04:51,409
What are you talking about?

110
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:53,330
Just stay home
and take care of your baby.

111
00:04:53,330 --> 00:04:54,530
I will definitely help you find

112
00:04:54,530 --> 00:04:55,600
Master, Mrs. Liu,

113
00:04:55,630 --> 00:04:57,159
and the Brigade Commander,

114
00:04:58,070 --> 00:04:59,070
Okay. Okay. Okay.

115
00:04:59,070 --> 00:05:00,270
We haven't pasted it there yet.

116
00:05:00,270 --> 00:05:01,020
Hurry up.

117
00:05:05,140 --> 00:05:06,800
I'll go to that intersection.

118
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:19,320
You're back.

119
00:05:23,110 --> 00:05:23,720
What's up?

120
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,650
Get the alcohol.

121
00:05:25,670 --> 00:05:27,780
Did you touch something dirty?

122
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:29,840
I just went to the refugee shelter.

123
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,900
It's too dirty inside.

124
00:05:33,430 --> 00:05:34,530
I saw an old person and a young dead,

125
00:05:34,530 --> 00:05:36,070
who hugged each other.

126
00:05:36,340 --> 00:05:38,159
No one could separate the bodies.

127
00:05:38,159 --> 00:05:39,000
Is it Uncle?

128
00:05:39,020 --> 00:05:40,300
No.

129
00:05:40,330 --> 00:05:41,530
I went to look for him.

130
00:05:42,070 --> 00:05:43,270
I searched the whole shelter

131
00:05:43,270 --> 00:05:44,950
but couldn't find him anywhere.

132
00:05:44,950 --> 00:05:45,800
Of course.

133
00:05:46,010 --> 00:05:47,430
The concession is quite big.

134
00:05:47,430 --> 00:05:49,290
Finding someone is not that easy.

135
00:05:50,490 --> 00:05:51,340
All right.

136
00:05:51,750 --> 00:05:52,800
Let me do it.

137
00:05:54,830 --> 00:05:57,520
Just now at Pushan Villa,

138
00:05:57,750 --> 00:05:58,150
Here you are.

139
00:05:58,150 --> 00:06:00,950
the corpse collector
from Red Swastika Society told me

140
00:06:00,950 --> 00:06:02,070
that they carried out

141
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:04,600
many dead bodies every day
from the shelter.

142
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:06,760
So, you mean Uncle might...

143
00:06:07,860 --> 00:06:09,120
Don't curse Uncle.

144
00:06:09,510 --> 00:06:11,390
Isn't that what you meant?

145
00:06:11,390 --> 00:06:12,940
No, I didn't.

146
00:06:13,570 --> 00:06:15,820
If Uncle is missing,

147
00:06:16,190 --> 00:06:18,390
what about the land deed
and the money he carried?

148
00:06:18,390 --> 00:06:19,470
Missy,

149
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:22,550
don't say things like that
at such a critical time.

150
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:24,140
Are you stupid?

151
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,880
If those things are gone,

152
00:06:26,210 --> 00:06:28,490
doesn't this house become ours?

153
00:06:28,670 --> 00:06:30,530
How many times do I have to tell you?

154
00:06:30,530 --> 00:06:32,200
We are here to look after this house,

155
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:33,640
not to seize it.

156
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:35,810
Can you stop being delusional?

157
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:39,220
I can think of anything.

158
00:06:39,350 --> 00:06:40,840
With your meager salary,

159
00:06:40,870 --> 00:06:42,110
why wouldn't I?

160
00:06:43,630 --> 00:06:44,680
What's more,

161
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:46,310
stop talking about

162
00:06:46,350 --> 00:06:48,000
your sister-in-law all the time.

163
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,640
You always think about her,

164
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,720
but when has she ever thought of you?

165
00:06:52,070 --> 00:06:53,159
Seriously.

166
00:06:59,070 --> 00:07:00,480
Without the land deed,

167
00:07:00,900 --> 00:07:02,600
they won't recognize your sister-in-law

168
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:03,560
as the landlord.

169
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,070
When Manager Hu comes,

170
00:07:05,070 --> 00:07:06,630
I won't be afraid of her
finding the truth.

171
00:07:06,630 --> 00:07:09,040
I don't have to lie all day long.

172
00:07:09,790 --> 00:07:10,830
Let your sister-in-law

173
00:07:10,830 --> 00:07:13,180
stay quietly in the attic.

174
00:07:13,750 --> 00:07:14,310
As for us,

175
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:17,090
we just need to take good care of Miss Liu
on the second floor.

176
00:07:17,090 --> 00:07:18,010
Anyway,

177
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:19,720
she will pay the rent in full.

178
00:07:20,430 --> 00:07:21,400
At most,

179
00:07:21,580 --> 00:07:24,710
we'll cook fish for your sister-in-law
a few more times.

180
00:07:24,710 --> 00:07:26,740
Isn't that good for everyone?

181
00:07:27,950 --> 00:07:29,580
When I asked for leave this morning,

182
00:07:29,580 --> 00:07:31,120
Manager Hu told me

183
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:34,330
that those outside tenants
must be kicked out,

184
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:36,140
otherwise, Miss Liu will move out.

185
00:07:36,140 --> 00:07:37,720
If Miss Liu moves out,

186
00:07:38,070 --> 00:07:40,040
my promotion to assistant manager
will be ruined.

187
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,640
Didn't Manager Hu promise us

188
00:07:41,659 --> 00:07:42,280
that by the end of this month,

189
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:44,010
he would finalize your promotion?

190
00:07:44,010 --> 00:07:46,630
So, nothing can go wrong now.

191
00:07:50,630 --> 00:07:52,490
Then, let's do as Manager Hu said.

192
00:07:52,530 --> 00:07:54,140
Miss Liu cannot move out.

193
00:07:54,940 --> 00:07:55,970
I'll find a way

194
00:07:56,060 --> 00:07:58,230
to kick all those tenants out.

195
00:08:00,610 --> 00:08:02,340
We have taken their money.

196
00:08:02,610 --> 00:08:03,800
They are living perfectly fine.

197
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:04,650
How can we kick them out?

198
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:06,480
But your promotion to assistant manager

199
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:07,830
is more important now!

200
00:08:10,010 --> 00:08:10,970
That's true.

201
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:14,080
Once I'm successfully promoted,

202
00:08:14,140 --> 00:08:16,340
my salary will double.

203
00:08:16,570 --> 00:08:19,160
It's much more stable
than collecting the rent.

204
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,050
Exactly.

205
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:21,740
We are at the final stage now.

206
00:08:22,070 --> 00:08:23,120
We can offend anyone,

207
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:25,040
but not the God of Wealth, Manager Hu.

208
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:26,760
You should play nice
with your sister-in-law.

209
00:08:26,760 --> 00:08:27,750
Then,

210
00:08:28,070 --> 00:08:29,670
that shifty-eyed orderly

211
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:31,020
wouldn't

212
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:32,169
mock us all day long.

213
00:09:15,980 --> 00:09:17,440
You don't even have a pair of shoes.

214
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:19,970
They were too heavy
when we crossed the river,

215
00:09:19,970 --> 00:09:20,980
so I threw them away.

216
00:09:20,980 --> 00:09:22,110
After crossing the river,

217
00:09:22,110 --> 00:09:24,320
everyone stripped clothes off the corpses,

218
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,980
but I thought it wasn't right.

219
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:27,540
Thinking about it now,

220
00:09:28,130 --> 00:09:29,250
I thought I was too naive back then.

221
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:31,910
Staying alive is more important
than anything.

222
00:09:32,950 --> 00:09:34,460
Come on, wrap your feet.

223
00:09:34,510 --> 00:09:34,910
At this rate,

224
00:09:34,910 --> 00:09:37,060
your feet will rot
before we reach the camp.

225
00:09:37,060 --> 00:09:37,920
Thank you, bro.

226
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:39,880
What are you two doing?

227
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:42,000
Sir, the kid has no shoes.

228
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:44,250
Blistered feet will affect his march.

229
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:52,330
Take these.

230
00:09:53,020 --> 00:09:53,880
Thank you, Sir.

231
00:09:56,170 --> 00:09:57,970
Hurry up. Don't delay marching.

232
00:10:06,740 --> 00:10:07,410
Come on.

233
00:10:09,530 --> 00:10:10,110
Can you make it?

234
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:10,950
Okay.

235
00:10:14,140 --> 00:10:15,140
What's your name?

236
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:16,500
My surname is Zhou.

237
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:17,770
Just call me Zhou.

238
00:10:19,030 --> 00:10:20,490
Sir, what's your surname?

239
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:24,020
My surname is Kong. My name is Kong Erbao.

240
00:10:24,110 --> 00:10:25,020
Brother Kong.

241
00:11:36,670 --> 00:11:37,960
Even written agreements

242
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:38,990
are invalid now, huh?

243
00:11:38,990 --> 00:11:40,320
Have you no conscience?

244
00:11:42,810 --> 00:11:43,950
Is there such logic?

245
00:11:44,580 --> 00:11:45,910
Is there no law anymore?

246
00:11:46,330 --> 00:11:47,760
How can you behave like this?

247
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:48,990
It breaks my heart.

248
00:11:49,140 --> 00:11:50,740
What is this world coming to?

249
00:11:51,250 --> 00:11:53,200
I'm worried to death.

250
00:11:53,270 --> 00:11:54,390
They asked us to move out.

251
00:11:54,390 --> 00:11:55,450
But where can we go?

252
00:11:55,470 --> 00:11:57,000
Auntie Liu, what happened?

253
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:01,720
Auntie Zhang, slow down.

254
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:06,230
They kick us out
even though we paid the rent.

255
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:12,970
With the old and the young,

256
00:12:12,990 --> 00:12:14,540
where can we go?

257
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:16,090
Miss Xu, are you moving too?

258
00:12:16,250 --> 00:12:18,450
I've never seen such a wicked landlord.

259
00:12:21,530 --> 00:12:22,840
Mrs. Zhang.

260
00:12:22,870 --> 00:12:24,320
When exactly is your relative
who is freeloading

261
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:25,670
going to leave?

262
00:12:25,910 --> 00:12:27,150
Her kid

263
00:12:27,170 --> 00:12:29,120
cries over my head day and night.

264
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:30,680
I have neurasthenia,

265
00:12:30,700 --> 00:12:31,820
you know that.

266
00:12:32,090 --> 00:12:33,670
How can I stand it?

267
00:12:33,730 --> 00:12:34,370
Yes.

268
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:36,390
Miss Liu, please bear with that.

269
00:12:36,420 --> 00:12:38,230
We'll take it one step at a time.

270
00:12:38,260 --> 00:12:39,580
But look at it.

271
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:41,800
I've already chased
those people outside away.

272
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:42,500
Rest assured

273
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:43,590
and leave this matter to me.

274
00:12:43,590 --> 00:12:44,770
I will definitely handle it for you.

275
00:12:44,770 --> 00:12:46,280
How are you going to handle it?

276
00:12:46,280 --> 00:12:47,520
Her little sidekick

277
00:12:47,540 --> 00:12:49,020
is a bum.

278
00:12:49,870 --> 00:12:50,730
He looks shifty-eyed.

279
00:12:50,730 --> 00:12:51,710
When he came and went,

280
00:12:51,710 --> 00:12:53,230
he always measured everything.

281
00:12:53,230 --> 00:12:54,670
You must put away your valuables

282
00:12:54,670 --> 00:12:56,030
at home.

283
00:12:56,350 --> 00:12:57,650
Miss Liu.

284
00:12:57,670 --> 00:12:59,530
It's all because my sister-in-law

285
00:12:59,530 --> 00:13:01,390
is shameless.

286
00:13:01,590 --> 00:13:03,400
She brings that rogue soldier

287
00:13:03,420 --> 00:13:04,840
to freeload.

288
00:13:04,970 --> 00:13:06,940
I'm just too soft-hearted.

289
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,050
But don't worry.

290
00:13:08,070 --> 00:13:08,670
In the next few days,

291
00:13:08,670 --> 00:13:10,670
I will definitely find a way
to kick him out.

292
00:13:10,670 --> 00:13:11,440
Whenever I look at him,

293
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:13,470
I just can't stand the sight of him.

294
00:13:19,030 --> 00:13:20,840
Who can't you stand the sight of?

295
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:22,720
And you,

296
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:25,010
who are you calling a country bumpkin?

297
00:13:25,370 --> 00:13:27,030
Who are you trying to kick out?

298
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:28,610
Let me tell you,

299
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:30,240
not a single tile

300
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:32,410
or brick in this house

301
00:13:32,430 --> 00:13:34,230
has anything to do with you.

302
00:13:34,260 --> 00:13:36,700
This is our Brigade Commander's house.

303
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:37,630
Madam is the only one who has the right

304
00:13:37,630 --> 00:13:39,870
to ask me to leave here.

305
00:13:39,890 --> 00:13:41,420
Our Brigade Commander and I

306
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:43,980
are life-and-death friends, you know?

307
00:13:44,010 --> 00:13:45,200
Who is it?

308
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:48,880
Who is a life-and-death friend
of Yunkui?

309
00:13:48,910 --> 00:13:50,240
Yunkui

310
00:13:50,770 --> 00:13:52,960
is a young general
from a scholarly family.

311
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:54,360
What exactly do you do?

312
00:13:54,710 --> 00:13:55,800
Stop talking.

313
00:13:57,560 --> 00:13:59,250
A porter?

314
00:13:59,270 --> 00:14:01,600
With your size, you can't
even carry a vat.

315
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:04,350
A servant?

316
00:14:04,370 --> 00:14:05,720
You can't read the air

317
00:14:05,750 --> 00:14:07,490
and don't know your place, either.

318
00:14:07,490 --> 00:14:08,400
A soldier?

319
00:14:08,840 --> 00:14:10,370
Wearing a belt here,

320
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:12,880
you don't seem like good grunt.

321
00:14:14,740 --> 00:14:15,740
Mr. Zhang,

322
00:14:16,340 --> 00:14:17,810
you stopped pretending, huh?

323
00:14:17,810 --> 00:14:19,820
You want to drop all pretenses, right?

324
00:14:19,820 --> 00:14:21,430
Bro, I'm just joking.

325
00:14:22,510 --> 00:14:24,020
The Zhang Family should thank you

326
00:14:24,020 --> 00:14:25,440
since you brought my sister-in-law home.

327
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:27,400
Your task is completed.

328
00:14:28,160 --> 00:14:28,810
No offense.

329
00:14:28,810 --> 00:14:29,690
Take this

330
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:31,980
to buy some spiced meat.

331
00:14:32,010 --> 00:14:33,260
No. No. No.

332
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,300
With this little money,

333
00:14:35,330 --> 00:14:37,050
you are playing the big shot
in front of me?

334
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:38,110
That's too shabby.

335
00:14:38,470 --> 00:14:40,190
I don't need your spiced meat.

336
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:43,450
You really have a problem.

337
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:45,140
You don't even want the money.

338
00:14:45,140 --> 00:14:47,610
That's Yunqi showing you sympathy.

339
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:49,960
You really don't know his kindness.

340
00:14:50,340 --> 00:14:51,230
Could it be that

341
00:14:51,260 --> 00:14:52,410
there are

342
00:14:52,870 --> 00:14:53,960
some attachments

343
00:14:53,990 --> 00:14:55,640
or something you're thinking about
in this family?

344
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:56,800
What do you mean?

345
00:14:57,360 --> 00:14:58,630
I don't mean anything.

346
00:14:58,750 --> 00:15:00,360
I just want you to know

347
00:15:00,380 --> 00:15:02,180
that we know

348
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:03,750
what you are plotting.

349
00:15:03,770 --> 00:15:05,770
Our sister-in-law has given birth,

350
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:06,530
but

351
00:15:06,650 --> 00:15:08,080
she still has a beautiful face
and slim waist,

352
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,200
and a nice figure.

353
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:11,230
She looks like a fairy.

354
00:15:11,260 --> 00:15:12,120
Tell me,

355
00:15:12,150 --> 00:15:14,790
how terrible it would be
if she was caught by a bad person.

356
00:15:14,790 --> 00:15:16,720
Dare you say it again?

357
00:15:16,740 --> 00:15:17,740
Watch your mouth!

358
00:15:18,270 --> 00:15:19,550
Mrs. Zhang, Mr. Zhang,

359
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:21,850
we are all decent people.

360
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:24,000
Look at how unreasonable he is.

361
00:15:24,020 --> 00:15:25,660
You can't reason with him.

362
00:15:25,690 --> 00:15:28,080
Just go to the police station
and get some officers.

363
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:29,480
Lock him up for a few days.

364
00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:30,960
Wouldn't that solve everything?

365
00:15:30,960 --> 00:15:31,450
Right?

366
00:15:33,260 --> 00:15:34,120
I'm sorry.

367
00:15:34,150 --> 00:15:35,670
I have a slight headache.

368
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:37,200
I'll go upstairs to rest.

369
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:37,840
Okay, take your time.

370
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:38,790
No, no, no.

371
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:40,640
You are all decent people, right?

372
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:41,400
Okay.

373
00:15:41,570 --> 00:15:43,140
Then let's have a decent chat.

374
00:15:43,140 --> 00:15:45,140
Who do you think you are? Step aside.

375
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:47,200
You're involved in this,

376
00:15:47,220 --> 00:15:48,430
Miss Liu, right?

377
00:15:48,880 --> 00:15:50,040
I'm having a decent talk with you guys.

378
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:51,520
I'm going to talk exactly about you.

379
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:52,040
Come on.

380
00:15:52,250 --> 00:15:52,920
Please sit.

381
00:15:53,030 --> 00:15:53,960
Please take the seat of honor.

382
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:54,910
What do you mean?

383
00:15:54,910 --> 00:15:56,120
What does it have to do with me?

384
00:15:56,120 --> 00:15:57,380
Miss Liu, Miss Liu, Miss Liu,

385
00:15:57,380 --> 00:15:58,560
don't stoop to his level.

386
00:15:58,560 --> 00:15:59,760
He has nothing to say.

387
00:15:59,770 --> 00:16:00,510
-Have a seat.
-Don't be afraid.

388
00:16:00,510 --> 00:16:02,570
-Don't be afraid.
-Have some hot tea.

389
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:07,790
Miss Liu,

390
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,370
I am a person

391
00:16:10,310 --> 00:16:11,620
who speaks bluntly.

392
00:16:12,430 --> 00:16:14,550
My eyes aren't very good

393
00:16:14,670 --> 00:16:15,510
at recognizing good people.

394
00:16:15,510 --> 00:16:17,050
But when it comes to spotting
scoundrels and sluts,

395
00:16:17,050 --> 00:16:18,360
I am spot on.

396
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:19,980
I heard

397
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:23,610
that Miss Liu is Mrs. Zhang's aunt,

398
00:16:23,630 --> 00:16:24,300
right?

399
00:16:24,430 --> 00:16:25,580
What's wrong with that?

400
00:16:25,580 --> 00:16:26,700
I just want to ask,

401
00:16:26,860 --> 00:16:27,570
Mrs. Zhang,

402
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:29,580
how many wives do your uncle have?

403
00:16:29,910 --> 00:16:31,360
Did your Grandma

404
00:16:31,380 --> 00:16:32,420
know that she has

405
00:16:32,450 --> 00:16:34,050
such a flirtatious daughter-in-law?

406
00:16:34,050 --> 00:16:34,920
Who are you talking about?

407
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:36,020
Don't get excited.

408
00:16:36,050 --> 00:16:36,840
What do you mean?

409
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:38,320
Don't get excited.

410
00:16:38,470 --> 00:16:41,550
We decent people are having
a decent chat, okay?

411
00:16:41,690 --> 00:16:43,720
Let's talk about another decent person,

412
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:44,760
Manager Hu.

413
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:46,050
Mr. Zhang,

414
00:16:46,530 --> 00:16:48,100
the foreign firm you work for

415
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:49,670
isn't far from home, is it?

416
00:16:49,990 --> 00:16:50,920
What do you mean?

417
00:16:51,020 --> 00:16:52,020
What's that mean?

418
00:16:52,230 --> 00:16:54,700
I passed by your firm the other day,

419
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:55,920
and coincidentally

420
00:16:55,920 --> 00:16:57,400
saw Manager Hu

421
00:16:57,420 --> 00:16:58,940
at your gate.

422
00:16:59,710 --> 00:17:01,910
I walked with him for a while,

423
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,130
and coincidentally

424
00:17:03,350 --> 00:17:05,420
we arrived at Manager Hu's house.

425
00:17:05,619 --> 00:17:07,790
His house is at

426
00:17:08,030 --> 00:17:11,770
Lane 36, Ferguson Road.

427
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:12,550
Brother.

428
00:17:12,550 --> 00:17:14,000
Don't listen to them.

429
00:17:14,020 --> 00:17:14,690
What are you doing?

430
00:17:14,690 --> 00:17:15,750
What are you doing?

431
00:17:15,819 --> 00:17:16,880
What are you doing?

432
00:17:17,650 --> 00:17:18,910
Act like a thug, huh?

433
00:17:18,930 --> 00:17:20,500
Act like a thug in front of me?

434
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:21,560
Can you outplay me?

435
00:17:21,980 --> 00:17:24,109
Before we finish our decent chat,

436
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:25,480
no one leaves.

437
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:29,910
No one even think about leaving.

438
00:17:29,910 --> 00:17:30,970
What are you doing?

439
00:17:36,820 --> 00:17:37,870
Come on.

440
00:17:38,270 --> 00:17:40,530
Let's talk about another decent person,

441
00:17:41,050 --> 00:17:41,860
Mrs. Hu.

442
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:44,940
Coincidentally that day,

443
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:46,310
at the door of Manager Hu's house,

444
00:17:46,310 --> 00:17:47,660
I met Mrs. Hu.

445
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:49,280
Mrs. Hu

446
00:17:49,560 --> 00:17:50,800
is tall.

447
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:52,160
She has thick arms

448
00:17:52,190 --> 00:17:53,630
and big ankles.

449
00:17:53,650 --> 00:17:54,570
When she walks,

450
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:56,180
she makes a loud clomping noise.

451
00:17:56,180 --> 00:17:58,040
The whole lane can hear her.

452
00:17:58,260 --> 00:17:59,180
Say it again.

453
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:00,640
I also coincidentally

454
00:18:00,870 --> 00:18:02,500
-saw Manager Hu
-Yunqi.

455
00:18:02,520 --> 00:18:03,160
Are you okay?

456
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:04,100
held

457
00:18:04,130 --> 00:18:06,290
an imported mink fur coat you like
in his left hand,

458
00:18:06,290 --> 00:18:08,790
and Wanlitai stockings in his right hand.

459
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:11,170
Manager Hu

460
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:12,440
was as tame as a cat in front of Mrs. Hu.

461
00:18:12,440 --> 00:18:13,280
What did you…

462
00:18:15,160 --> 00:18:16,530
I also have a loose tongue.

463
00:18:16,530 --> 00:18:18,330
I found out that Mrs. Hu

464
00:18:18,510 --> 00:18:20,030
-likes watermelon.
-Are you okay?

465
00:18:20,030 --> 00:18:21,400
When she eats watermelon,

466
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:23,180
she never uses a knife.

467
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:26,070
She uses her hands

468
00:18:26,560 --> 00:18:28,250
to cut it off.

469
00:18:28,950 --> 00:18:30,020
You are a hooligan.

470
00:18:30,690 --> 00:18:31,830
Mrs. Zhang! Mrs. Zhang!

471
00:18:31,830 --> 00:18:33,820
You are a bum!

472
00:18:37,720 --> 00:18:39,260
Call the police station.

473
00:18:40,270 --> 00:18:41,560
Mrs. Zhang, are you okay?

474
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:42,790
What's wrong with you?

475
00:18:42,790 --> 00:18:43,830
Miss Liu,

476
00:18:44,250 --> 00:18:45,100
how is it?

477
00:18:45,130 --> 00:18:47,990
I will go get Manager Hu

478
00:18:48,030 --> 00:18:49,890
and Mrs. Hu here right now.

479
00:18:50,040 --> 00:18:51,110
Let them officially recognize you

480
00:18:51,110 --> 00:18:54,590
as their sworn sister here.

481
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:57,720
Brother.

482
00:18:57,740 --> 00:18:58,590
what are you doing?

483
00:18:58,590 --> 00:18:59,090
Listen to me.

484
00:18:59,090 --> 00:18:59,550
Move away.

485
00:18:59,550 --> 00:19:00,270
Brother, brother.

486
00:19:00,270 --> 00:19:00,740
Move away.

487
00:19:00,740 --> 00:19:01,880
Let's talk this out.

488
00:19:02,160 --> 00:19:03,730
Horrible! Horrible!

489
00:19:03,770 --> 00:19:05,480
I really can't live here anymore.

490
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:06,490
Who the hell are you?

491
00:19:06,490 --> 00:19:07,550
We can talk it over.

492
00:19:07,570 --> 00:19:09,300
Let me tell you,
I couldn't stand it long ago.

493
00:19:09,300 --> 00:19:10,880
I've wanted to leave for a long time.

494
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:11,400
Miss Liu.

495
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:13,400
-Miss Liu. Miss Liu.
-I'll move now.

496
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:15,420
Go pick up Manager Hu.

497
00:19:15,670 --> 00:19:16,840
Miss Liu,

498
00:19:17,260 --> 00:19:19,050
listen to me.

499
00:19:19,390 --> 00:19:20,630
Miss Liu.

500
00:19:21,860 --> 00:19:24,090
Miss Liu, please listen to me.

501
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:28,500
We haven't finished our decent chat yet.

502
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:30,400
Are we still chatting or not?

503
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:39,160
A beauty half-hidden behind the door.

504
00:19:39,890 --> 00:19:42,090
Now you've got exactly what you wanted.

505
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:44,100
Shuyuan, what do you mean?

506
00:19:45,090 --> 00:19:47,790
Pretending to be something you're not

507
00:19:48,090 --> 00:19:49,570
is like playing dumb.

508
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:50,890
Sister-in-law,

509
00:19:51,100 --> 00:19:53,540
we've been together for so long.

510
00:19:53,850 --> 00:19:56,450
I didn't realize what a person you are
till now.

511
00:19:57,440 --> 00:19:58,500
Basking in the sun?

512
00:19:59,430 --> 00:20:01,030
Basking in the sun is so nice.

513
00:20:01,370 --> 00:20:03,640
It can kill off all those

514
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:05,310
crooked ways.

515
00:20:06,470 --> 00:20:08,730
Well, Shuyuan, you said that quite well.

516
00:20:10,250 --> 00:20:12,190
Crooked ways that can't see the light

517
00:20:12,190 --> 00:20:13,790
need to be exposed to the sun.

518
00:21:00,230 --> 00:21:02,790
♪ In spring, a hundred flowers bloom ♪

519
00:21:02,810 --> 00:21:05,280
♪ Lang li ge,
lang li ge, lang li ge lang ♪

520
00:21:06,370 --> 00:21:07,830
Madam, look,

521
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:08,980
how nice this big terrace is.

522
00:21:08,980 --> 00:21:11,180
The kid can bask in the sun here.

523
00:21:11,430 --> 00:21:13,760
♪ The warm sun is shining in the sky ♪

524
00:21:13,790 --> 00:21:16,020
♪ Shines on my ragged clothes ♪

525
00:21:16,050 --> 00:21:18,410
♪ Lang li ge lang, lang li ge lang ♪

526
00:21:18,510 --> 00:21:20,920
♪ Through the big streets
and small alleys ♪

527
00:21:20,990 --> 00:21:23,360
small alleys, small alleys...

528
00:21:24,610 --> 00:21:26,590
What's the point of
making indirect accusations?

529
00:21:26,590 --> 00:21:27,480
So what?

530
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:28,070
In all my life,

531
00:21:28,070 --> 00:21:29,150
I've never been bullied like this.

532
00:21:29,150 --> 00:21:30,960
No, you're acting like
a child playing house.

533
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:32,240
Is it any interesting?

534
00:21:32,270 --> 00:21:32,960
It is interesting.

535
00:21:32,960 --> 00:21:33,950
I'll count to three, let go of me.

536
00:21:33,950 --> 00:21:34,210
No.

537
00:21:34,230 --> 00:21:34,920
Three.

538
00:21:36,550 --> 00:21:37,280
Shuyuan.

539
00:21:43,120 --> 00:21:45,120
You've moved into the house, right?

540
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:47,280
The bed is big enough, right?

541
00:21:47,670 --> 00:21:49,620
Lying horizontally or vertically,

542
00:21:49,620 --> 00:21:51,280
you can even roll around in it.

543
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:53,720
Much more comfortable
than your attic, right?

544
00:21:53,720 --> 00:21:55,520
You must be thrilled.

545
00:21:55,550 --> 00:21:57,590
Your nose is up in the air, right?

546
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,420
But we are miserable.

547
00:21:59,890 --> 00:22:01,500
Zhang Yunqi, let me tell you,

548
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:02,630
offending Mr. Hu

549
00:22:02,660 --> 00:22:04,590
will definitely cost you your job.

550
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:06,770
I just don't understand.

551
00:22:06,890 --> 00:22:09,300
I collected some rent to subsidize
our household expenses.

552
00:22:09,300 --> 00:22:10,790
What crime did I commit?

553
00:22:10,810 --> 00:22:12,730
Why do you have to drive us
to a dead end?

554
00:22:12,730 --> 00:22:14,460
You want to wipe us all out, huh?

555
00:22:14,960 --> 00:22:17,240
You only dare to bully Yunqi.

556
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:18,820
I'm telling you,

557
00:22:19,330 --> 00:22:21,330
if Yunqi loses his job,

558
00:22:21,350 --> 00:22:23,680
no one in this family
will have a good time.

559
00:22:24,050 --> 00:22:26,540
If you want to live in a nice room,
just say so.

560
00:22:26,810 --> 00:22:29,050
Why did you play good cop and bad cop?

561
00:22:29,070 --> 00:22:31,510
You really treat yourself
like Her Ladyship.

562
00:22:31,510 --> 00:22:33,870
You even bring an orderly everywhere.

563
00:22:34,250 --> 00:22:35,960
Looking so shifty-eyed,

564
00:22:36,010 --> 00:22:38,400
he doesn't look like a soldier at all.

565
00:22:38,570 --> 00:22:40,910
A lone man and a lone woman
are in a compromising situation.

566
00:22:40,910 --> 00:22:42,510
Do you really think others are fools?

567
00:22:42,510 --> 00:22:43,890
-It's too hard...
-People know

568
00:22:43,890 --> 00:22:45,240
what you think.

569
00:22:45,650 --> 00:22:47,970
Don't make me spell it out.

570
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:49,660
Stop talking. It's too awful.

571
00:22:51,460 --> 00:22:53,710
You're a wicked person
pretending to be good.

572
00:22:53,710 --> 00:22:56,270
You really think yourself a decent woman.

573
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:00,820
They are asking
for a scolding again.

574
00:23:01,580 --> 00:23:06,050
♪ Family ties are treated
like floating duckweed ♪

575
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:10,680
♪ They bully the poor, favor the rich,
and disown their own family ♪

576
00:23:10,920 --> 00:23:15,000
♪ Snobbish people are truly hateful ♪

577
00:23:15,630 --> 00:23:17,610
Truly hateful!

578
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:20,380
Dalang, it's time to take your medicine.

579
00:23:20,460 --> 00:23:22,180
Kill you bitch!

580
00:23:28,630 --> 00:23:29,480
Avenge me!

581
00:23:29,960 --> 00:23:31,730
Hit them! I can't.

582
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:35,720
Stab the floor! No.

583
00:23:35,740 --> 00:23:36,500
Three!

584
00:23:42,670 --> 00:23:43,270
Attack!

585
00:23:50,460 --> 00:23:51,920
Playing this with me, huh?

586
00:23:53,260 --> 00:23:54,490
I can also use this trick.

587
00:23:54,490 --> 00:23:55,790
I can also use this trick.

588
00:23:55,790 --> 00:23:56,590
I can also use this trick.

589
00:23:56,590 --> 00:23:57,920
I'll stomp you to death.

590
00:23:58,710 --> 00:23:59,640
Okay.

591
00:24:00,110 --> 00:24:01,830
Coming together, huh?

592
00:24:02,100 --> 00:24:03,690
Is that what you want?

593
00:24:05,950 --> 00:24:07,250
I'll stomp you to death! I'll stomp!

594
00:24:07,250 --> 00:24:08,290
I stomp! Stomp! Stomp!

595
00:24:08,290 --> 00:24:09,000
I'll stomp you to death!

596
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:10,550
Stomp you to death!

597
00:24:10,690 --> 00:24:11,320
Stomp you to death!

598
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:12,350
I'll stomp you to death!

599
00:24:12,350 --> 00:24:13,650
Stomp you to death!

600
00:24:17,370 --> 00:24:18,610
I'll stomp you to death!

601
00:24:18,610 --> 00:24:20,410
I will stomp you to death!

602
00:24:21,740 --> 00:24:23,400
Come on, let's do it together.

603
00:24:45,580 --> 00:24:47,520
Yunqi, hurry up.

604
00:24:48,810 --> 00:24:50,010
It's full of dust.

605
00:24:50,040 --> 00:24:51,680
I told you to stop.

606
00:24:51,700 --> 00:24:52,900
The house is about to collapse.

607
00:24:52,900 --> 00:24:54,240
Then what should we do?

608
00:24:54,460 --> 00:24:55,210
Stomp!

609
00:24:55,230 --> 00:24:56,080
Stomp dust all over your bed.

610
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:56,920
Stomp dust all over your bed.

611
00:24:56,920 --> 00:24:58,270
Wanfu, stop.

612
00:24:59,050 --> 00:24:59,790
What, Madam?

613
00:25:00,360 --> 00:25:01,670
-Forget it.
-I'll stomp them with dust.

614
00:25:01,670 --> 00:25:03,050
Stomp dust all over your bed.

615
00:25:03,050 --> 00:25:04,000
Stop stomping.

616
00:25:09,810 --> 00:25:10,680
Listen.

617
00:25:11,140 --> 00:25:12,340
They stopped, right?

618
00:25:12,790 --> 00:25:13,850
Stomp you to death.

619
00:25:14,430 --> 00:25:15,260
Forget it.

620
00:25:15,810 --> 00:25:17,210
They are afraid of me now.

621
00:25:24,650 --> 00:25:25,850
What's wrong, Madam?

622
00:25:27,330 --> 00:25:29,190
I don't want to live here anymore.

623
00:25:30,220 --> 00:25:31,330
Let's move back to the attic.

624
00:25:31,330 --> 00:25:32,660
Have you lost your mind?

625
00:25:32,930 --> 00:25:33,720
We fought hard

626
00:25:33,720 --> 00:25:34,990
to get this room back.

627
00:25:35,040 --> 00:25:36,000
No, it's not.

628
00:25:36,250 --> 00:25:37,650
When villains fight, they both get hurt.

629
00:25:37,650 --> 00:25:38,480
If we fight against them,

630
00:25:38,480 --> 00:25:39,740
what does that make us?

631
00:25:40,730 --> 00:25:42,860
Can't you see they are playing rogue?

632
00:25:43,120 --> 00:25:44,090
To deal with rogues,

633
00:25:44,090 --> 00:25:46,080
we must use their methods

634
00:25:46,100 --> 00:25:47,270
and be even more rogue.

635
00:25:47,270 --> 00:25:48,160
Today,

636
00:25:48,440 --> 00:25:51,060
they poke the ceiling with a broom
on the first floor,

637
00:25:51,060 --> 00:25:52,530
and you jump on the second floor.

638
00:25:52,530 --> 00:25:54,340
Tomorrow, if they continue poking,

639
00:25:54,340 --> 00:25:55,470
you want me to stomp?

640
00:25:55,880 --> 00:25:56,660
What about the day after tomorrow,

641
00:25:56,660 --> 00:25:57,860
or the day after that?

642
00:25:59,310 --> 00:26:00,240
Just forget it.

643
00:26:00,510 --> 00:26:02,170
We might as well move back to the attic.

644
00:26:02,170 --> 00:26:03,690
With a floor between us,

645
00:26:04,790 --> 00:26:06,140
I can get peace.

646
00:26:08,140 --> 00:26:08,830
Madam.

647
00:26:10,290 --> 00:26:11,820
You can't give up this room.

648
00:26:11,820 --> 00:26:12,900
Nobody else can live in this room

649
00:26:12,900 --> 00:26:13,940
but you.

650
00:26:14,440 --> 00:26:16,110
This house was originally yours.

651
00:26:16,110 --> 00:26:18,260
You are the Eldest Young Mistress
of the Zhang family.

652
00:26:18,260 --> 00:26:20,740
It is your right
to live in this room.

653
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:22,920
Sit back down.

654
00:26:24,420 --> 00:26:25,520
Sit down.

655
00:26:43,040 --> 00:26:43,760
Madam.

656
00:26:43,880 --> 00:26:45,150
Do you know why

657
00:26:45,170 --> 00:26:46,970
they dare to bully you like this?

658
00:26:47,230 --> 00:26:49,760
They are betting that Master
can't come back.

659
00:26:51,270 --> 00:26:52,300
Have you ever thought about

660
00:26:52,300 --> 00:26:54,030
what if Master can't come back?

661
00:26:54,650 --> 00:26:55,850
I mean what if

662
00:26:55,870 --> 00:26:56,990
he can't come back,

663
00:26:57,010 --> 00:26:58,320
and you vacate this room,

664
00:26:58,320 --> 00:26:58,940
let me tell you,

665
00:26:58,940 --> 00:27:00,030
tomorrow, they

666
00:27:00,050 --> 00:27:01,040
will kick both of you

667
00:27:01,040 --> 00:27:02,300
out to the street to sleep.

668
00:27:02,300 --> 00:27:03,300
Believe it or not.

669
00:27:03,760 --> 00:27:05,650
But we are a family anyway.

670
00:27:06,320 --> 00:27:07,850
They can't be that vicious.

671
00:27:08,240 --> 00:27:10,080
Vicious? You call this vicious?

672
00:27:10,330 --> 00:27:11,000
Madam,

673
00:27:11,270 --> 00:27:12,750
you grew up in a honeypot.

674
00:27:12,770 --> 00:27:14,770
You don't know what viciousness is.

675
00:27:14,880 --> 00:27:17,640
You may know a person's face,
but not their heart.

676
00:27:18,030 --> 00:27:20,140
You haven't seen real viciousness.

677
00:27:20,310 --> 00:27:21,110
For instance.

678
00:27:21,530 --> 00:27:22,240
you hate

679
00:27:22,630 --> 00:27:23,890
the couple, don't you?

680
00:27:24,410 --> 00:27:25,780
But let me tell you,

681
00:27:26,050 --> 00:27:27,510
in my eyes,

682
00:27:27,820 --> 00:27:29,290
they are quite normal.

683
00:27:29,510 --> 00:27:30,600
If I were them,

684
00:27:30,860 --> 00:27:33,190
I would shamelessly be the sublessor too.

685
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:34,200
I would also hoard Japanese goods.

686
00:27:34,200 --> 00:27:36,060
I would also profit from
the national crisis.

687
00:27:36,060 --> 00:27:38,480
It's normal for them to
bully a widow and her orphan?

688
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:39,760
They let you sleep in the attic.

689
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:40,520
If it were me,

690
00:27:40,550 --> 00:27:41,310
I would throw you directly

691
00:27:41,310 --> 00:27:43,210
into the kitchen to sleep on the floor.

692
00:27:43,210 --> 00:27:44,870
That's what you call vicious.

693
00:27:45,010 --> 00:27:46,230
In this world,

694
00:27:47,010 --> 00:27:48,460
only petty people are vicious.

695
00:27:48,460 --> 00:27:50,540
But relying on viciousness,

696
00:27:50,570 --> 00:27:51,450
petty people can live comfortably.

697
00:27:51,450 --> 00:27:52,650
They live at ease.

698
00:27:52,680 --> 00:27:53,940
What about gentlemen?

699
00:27:54,750 --> 00:27:56,390
You, Master,

700
00:27:56,600 --> 00:27:57,580
and our Brigade Commander

701
00:27:57,580 --> 00:27:59,430
are all gentle.

702
00:27:59,590 --> 00:28:01,860
You're all like clean walnuts.

703
00:28:02,070 --> 00:28:03,420
But in my eyes,

704
00:28:03,570 --> 00:28:04,920
you are all big fools,

705
00:28:04,940 --> 00:28:06,600
each stupider than the other.

706
00:28:06,830 --> 00:28:08,100
He is your Brigade Commander.

707
00:28:08,100 --> 00:28:09,680
How can you say that about him?

708
00:28:09,680 --> 00:28:10,480
Yes.

709
00:28:10,620 --> 00:28:13,280
My Brigade Commander
risked his life to save me.

710
00:28:13,350 --> 00:28:15,610
I will be grateful to him
for the rest of my life.

711
00:28:15,610 --> 00:28:16,510
From the bottom of my heart,

712
00:28:16,510 --> 00:28:18,440
I thank him a million times.

713
00:28:18,460 --> 00:28:20,320
I will never forget him in my life.

714
00:28:20,430 --> 00:28:22,210
If I didn't even have
this bit of gratitude,

715
00:28:22,210 --> 00:28:23,770
I wouldn't deserve to be a human.

716
00:28:23,770 --> 00:28:25,370
But gratitude is gratitude.

717
00:28:25,490 --> 00:28:27,290
Madam, let me tell you the truth.

718
00:28:27,490 --> 00:28:29,540
Our Brigade Commander is just stupid.

719
00:28:29,540 --> 00:28:32,000
He risked his life to save
a worm like me.

720
00:28:32,400 --> 00:28:33,490
He abandoned his own father,

721
00:28:33,490 --> 00:28:35,170
his own wife and kid,

722
00:28:35,440 --> 00:28:36,950
and even sacrificed himself.

723
00:28:36,950 --> 00:28:38,110
If I were our Brigade Commander,

724
00:28:38,110 --> 00:28:39,480
I wouldn't even save myself.

725
00:28:39,480 --> 00:28:41,380
Don't you think Zhang Yunkui
is a big fool?

726
00:28:41,380 --> 00:28:43,480
You know he saved you,
yet you still talk about him like this.

727
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:45,330
Just be a worm for the rest of your life.

728
00:28:45,330 --> 00:28:46,480
What are you doing?

729
00:28:46,770 --> 00:28:48,440
Why are you getting mad at me?

730
00:28:48,770 --> 00:28:50,250
So what if I'm a worm?

731
00:28:50,620 --> 00:28:51,640
I am a worm.

732
00:28:51,760 --> 00:28:52,680
You think I'm a worm.

733
00:28:52,680 --> 00:28:53,910
The Brigade Commander thinks I'm a worm.

734
00:28:53,910 --> 00:28:55,640
People of the Zhang family
all think I'm a worm.

735
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:56,470
But let me tell you,

736
00:28:56,470 --> 00:28:57,270
in this world,

737
00:28:57,300 --> 00:28:59,430
only worms can survive.

738
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:02,600
A living dog is better than a dead lion.

739
00:29:02,600 --> 00:29:04,530
Every man for himself.

740
00:29:05,030 --> 00:29:06,950
Our Brigade Commander didn't
look out for himself.

741
00:29:06,950 --> 00:29:08,080
And what was his end?

742
00:29:08,090 --> 00:29:09,900
He was destroyed!

743
00:29:10,760 --> 00:29:12,410
He was torn to pieces.

744
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:13,310
Even when he died,

745
00:29:13,310 --> 00:29:14,920
he didn't get to see his own son.

746
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:15,790
I feel wronged for him.

747
00:29:15,790 --> 00:29:16,800
I feel sad for him.

748
00:29:16,820 --> 00:29:18,690
I feel it wasn't worth it.

749
00:29:19,180 --> 00:29:21,240
If this is what's truly in your heart,

750
00:29:21,700 --> 00:29:23,250
I have finally seen clearly today

751
00:29:23,250 --> 00:29:24,780
what kind of person you are.

752
00:29:24,780 --> 00:29:25,980
You just insulted him,

753
00:29:25,980 --> 00:29:28,830
but now you hypocritically
say you feel wronged for him,

754
00:29:28,830 --> 00:29:29,700
sad for him,

755
00:29:29,730 --> 00:29:31,260
and that it wasn't worth it.

756
00:29:32,010 --> 00:29:33,540
What kind of person are you?

757
00:29:33,580 --> 00:29:34,780
Are you worthy?

758
00:29:36,570 --> 00:29:38,310
Do you think your Brigade Commander

759
00:29:38,310 --> 00:29:40,640
died because of you, an orderly?

760
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:42,070
Do you think your Brigade Commander

761
00:29:42,070 --> 00:29:44,470
died to save a worm like you?

762
00:29:44,550 --> 00:29:47,190
He died for his dream.

763
00:29:47,590 --> 00:29:49,990
He died because
he had a broad perspective!

764
00:29:50,240 --> 00:29:51,080
You?

765
00:29:51,870 --> 00:29:52,750
You?

766
00:29:53,030 --> 00:29:53,960
You, Meng Wanfu,

767
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:55,750
